params.name: pixel_values
params.type: jnp.ndarray of shape (batch_size, num_channels, height, width)
params.description: Pixel values. Pixel values can be obtained using the vision models image processor. For example, usingAutoImageProcessor. See ViTImageProcessor.call() for details.

params.name: decoder_input_ids
params.description: Indices of decoder input sequence tokens in the vocabulary.Indices can be obtained using PreTrainedTokenizer. See PreTrainedTokenizer.encode() andPreTrainedTokenizer.call() for details.What are decoder input IDs?

params.name: decoder_attention_mask
params.description: Default behavior: generate a tensor that ignores pad tokens in decoder_input_ids. Causal mask will alsobe used by default.

params.name: decoder_position_ids
params.description: Indices of positions of each decoder input sequence tokens in the position embeddings. Selected in therange [0, config.decoder.max_position_embeddings - 1].

params.name: output_attentions
params.description: Whether or not to return the attentions tensors of all attention layers. See attentions under returnedtensors for more detail.

params.name: output_hidden_states
params.description: Whether or not to return the hidden states of all layers. See hidden_states under returned tensors formore detail.

params.name: return_dict
params.description: If set to True, the model will return a ~utils.FlaxSeq2SeqLMOutput instead of a plain tuple.
